defs.docs: Asynchronous synchronization primitives.

A multi-producer, single-consumer queue for sending values across
 asynchronous tasks.

 tasks.

defs.docs: Thread-safe, asynchronous counting semaphore.

defs.name: Semaphore
defs.docs: Futures-aware semaphore.

defs.name: Permit
defs.docs: A semaphore permit

defs.docs: Error returned by `Permit::poll_acquire`.

defs.docs: Error returned by `Permit::try_acquire`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new semaphore with the initial number of permits

defs.name: available_permits
defs.docs: Returns the current number of available permits

defs.name: close
defs.docs:
Close the semaphore. This prevents the semaphore from issuing new
 permits and notifies all pending waiters.

defs.name: add_permits
defs.docs: Add `n` new permits to the semaphore.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new `Permit`.

defs.name: is_acquired
defs.docs: Returns true if the permit has been acquired

defs.name: poll_acquire
defs.docs:
Try to acquire the permit. If no permits are available, the current task
 is notified once a new permit becomes available.

defs.name: try_acquire
defs.docs: Try to acquire the permit.

defs.name: release
defs.docs: Release a permit back to the semaphore

defs.name: forget
defs.docs: Forget the permit **without** releasing it back to the semaphore.

defs.name: is_closed
defs.docs: Returns true if the error was caused by a closed semaphore.

defs.name: is_no_permits
defs.docs:
Returns true if the error was caused by calling `try_acquire` on a
 semaphore with no available permits.

defs.name: task
defs.docs: Thread-safe task notification primitives.

defs.docs: A synchronization primitive for task notification.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create an `AtomicTask` initialized with the given `Task`

defs.name: register
defs.docs: Registers the current task to be notified on calls to `notify`.

defs.name: register_task
defs.docs: Registers the provided task to be notified on calls to `notify`.

defs.name: notify
defs.docs: Notifies the task that last called `register`.

defs.name: take_task
defs.docs:
Attempts to take the `Task` value out of the `AtomicTask` with the
 intention that the caller will notify the task later.

A single-producer, multi-consumer channel that only retains the *last* sent
